This past week I've seen some things. I've seen huge lines of division, but perhaps not the "division" you might be thinking of. This division I speak of is the "good kind" of division, because it's the same division that separates wheat from chaff. We have many, many truly beautiful, talented, noble White people in this movement. These people are really dedicated to making great change. A lot of these people make big sacrifices for our cause- whether it's organizing events and fundraisers, printing literature, doing street activism or anonymously contributing financially. Some people just show up and find their place in irl community. Regardless of the ways we engage, we tend to be attracted to one another and can typically, quickly identify like minds. We then naturally form concentric rings of social circles among each other. However, outside that network, there exists a slithering cesspool of darkness and misery in the online world, which consists of hopelessly anonymous haters and fools who do nothing for our people. They might think they're part of the movement, but they are not. Their only purpose is to serve their own narcissistic tendencies by typing characters on the internet or gaining false fame. I've seen the things they produce, and their contributions to our people amount to nothing more than a pile of back alley garbage. That darkness tries to pretend it's important. Do not fall for it. Stay focused on what is REAL. The road to victory for our people is not easy. Our ancestors valued stories, so much so that the tradition of bardic song is known by all. If the path to victory were a simple one, there'd be no story to tell. Be wise of where and whom you give your precious energy. And do not despair if your "vehicle" breaks down. Fix it, or find a better one. Hail Victory! Hail the Folk! Hail WHITE UNITY ü§ç
